<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5176990>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Therates spec., left = ventral view, right = dorsal view: (1) mandible, (2) labrum, (3) clypeus, (4) eye, (5) orbital plate, (6) pronotum, (7) lateral line, (8) middle line, (9) scutellum, (10) basal hump, (11) apical hump, (12) apical dot, (13) central dot, (14) humeral lunule, (15) basal dot, (16) transverse furrows, (17) antenna, (18) frons, (19) maxillary palpus, (20) labial palpus, (21) mesoepisternum, (22) epipleurum, (23) ventrites. Scale = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5176990/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5176992>
    dc:description "Figures 3. Provisional arrangement of species of the chennelli group following the results of cladistic analysis." ;
